claim.claim-text:
1. An artificial fibrocartilage implant comprising:
an arcuate or torroidal bioresorbable scaffold;
a network of circumferential bioresorable fibers independent from and embedded in said scaffold; and
a network of orthogonal bioresorbable fibers independent from and embedded in said scaffold to prevent separation of said circumferential fiber network;
wherein the bioresorbable circumferential fibers and the bioresorbable orthogonal fibers define a reinforcing matrix having a three-dimensional shape and geometry which is substantially the same as the three-dimensional shape and geometry of the bioresorbable scaffold so as to convert an axial compressive force on said bioresorbable scaffold to tensile loads along the network of circumferential bioresorbable fibers.
